Dorsal plates with small hemispherical granules/upper ends of cuticular pillars (dots in PCM) 0.5–1.2 μm in diameter, densely (spaces between granules 0.5–0.8 μm) and uniformly distributed and joined by thin striae forming indistinct hexagonal pattern (which are in fact thin stripes positioned under epicuticle) (
Fig. 5A
). Granules/upper ends of cuticular pillars slightly larger in the anterior and posterior parts of the plates.
